Run at Python 3.7.6

1 - Clone project
2 - Install dependencies
3 - Run Redis on port 6379 (docker run -p 6379:6379 -d redis:2.8)
4 - Run migrations
5 - Runserver
6 - Access http://127.0.0.1:8000/
7 - Create superuser
8 - Aceess http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin and create a new Item
9 - Behold the channels working with the Django signals


SOURCE
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46614541/using-django-signals-in-channels-consumer-classes
